Copper gained for the first time in
six days after the U.S. Federal Reserve pledged to keep its
benchmark  interest rate  at a record low through at least
mid-2013, and imports of the metal into  China  rose for a second
month.  Market News:  Metals News:  To contact the reporter on this story:
